 "finding": "|D31*| grows toward the Shaing-Callen value as nuPrime drops, crosses the asymptote near the recorded nuPrime, and at EStar = 0 keeps deepening below it through nuPrime = 3e-4: the 1/nu-regime offset does not decay without orbit precession.  The small finite EStar = 3e-3 curve detaches from the EStar = 0 curve below nuPrime ~ 1e-3 and flattens back toward the asymptote (ExB precession); the dropped exploratory 1e-4 point continues both trends."
